{
  "video_id": "6d6oq0zGGmw",
  "title": "The brain may be able to repair itself -- with help | Jocelyne Bloch",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12896.0,
      "end_time": 14579.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;m a neurosurgeon."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15746.0,
      "end_time": 17649.0,
      "text": "And like most of my colleagues,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17673.0,
      "end_time": 21328.0,
      "text": "I have to deal, every day, with human tragedies."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22549.0,
      "end_time": 27354.0,
      "text": "I realize how your life can change from one second to the other"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27378.0,
      "end_time": 31423.0,
      "text": "after a major stroke or after a car accident."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 32450.000000000004,
      "end_time": 35783.0,
      "text": "And what is very frustrating for us neurosurgeons"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 35807.0,
      "end_time": 40427.0,
      "text": "is to realize that unlike other organs of the body,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 40451.0,
      "end_time": 43930.0,
      "text": "the brain has very little ability for self-repair."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 45211.0,
      "end_time": 49125.0,
      "text": "And after a major injury of your central nervous system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 50365.0,
      "end_time": 54125.0,
      "text": "the patients often remain with a severe handicap."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 55203.0,
      "end_time": 57416.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s probably the reason why I&#39;ve chosen"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 57440.0,
      "end_time": 60102.0,
      "text": "to be a functional neurosurgeon."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 61144.0,
      "end_time": 63520.0,
      "text": "What is a functional neurosurgeon?"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 63978.0,
      "end_time": 68338.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a doctor who is trying to improve a neurological function"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 68362.0,
      "end_time": 70679.0,
      "text": "through different surgical strategies."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 72660.0,
      "end_time": 74376.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ve certainly heard of one of the famous ones"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 74400.0,
      "end_time": 76486.0,
      "text": "called deep brain stimulation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 77230.0,
      "end_time": 81362.0,
      "text": "where you implant an electrode in the depths of the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 81386.0,
      "end_time": 84961.0,
      "text": "in order to modulate a circuit of neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 84986.0,
      "end_time": 86878.0,
      "text": "to improve a neurological function."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 87330.0,
      "end_time": 89396.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s really an amazing technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 89420.0,
      "end_time": 92787.0,
      "text": "in that it has improved the destiny of patients"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 92811.0,
      "end_time": 94633.0,
      "text": "with Parkinson&#39;s disease,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 94657.0,
      "end_time": 97762.0,
      "text": "with severe tremor, with severe pain."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 98870.0,
      "end_time": 104456.0,
      "text": "However, neuromodulation does not mean neuro-repair."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 105301.0,
      "end_time": 107608.0,
      "text": "And the dream of functional neurosurgeons"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 107632.0,
      "end_time": 109270.0,
      "text": "is to repair the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 111222.0,
      "end_time": 112619.0,
      "text": "I think"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 112643.0,
      "end_time": 114478.0,
      "text": "that we are approaching this dream."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 114502.0,
      "end_time": 116134.0,
      "text": "And I would like to show you"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 117161.0,
      "end_time": 119960.0,
      "text": "that we are very close to this."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 120220.0,
      "end_time": 123133.0,
      "text": "And that with a little bit of help,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 123157.0,
      "end_time": 126524.0,
      "text": "the brain is able to help itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 128514.99999999999,
      "end_time": 130684.99999999999,
      "text": "So the story started 15 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 131156.0,
      "end_time": 133176.0,
      "text": "At that time, I was a chief resident"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 133200.0,
      "end_time": 136113.0,
      "text": "working days and nights in the emergency room."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 136619.0,
      "end_time": 139828.0,
      "text": "I often had to take care of patients with head trauma."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 141193.0,
      "end_time": 145654.0,
      "text": "You have to imagine that when a patient comes in with a severe head trauma,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 145678.0,
      "end_time": 147977.0,
      "text": "his brain is swelling"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 148100.0,
      "end_time": 150981.0,
      "text": "and he&#39;s increasing his intracranial pressure."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 151716.0,
      "end_time": 153945.0,
      "text": "And in order to save his life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 153969.0,
      "end_time": 156777.0,
      "text": "you have to decrease this intracranial pressure."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 156801.0,
      "end_time": 157952.0,
      "text": "And to do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 157976.0,
      "end_time": 161896.0,
      "text": "you sometimes have to remove a piece of swollen brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 162587.0,
      "end_time": 166935.0,
      "text": "So instead of throwing away these pieces of swollen brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 166959.0,
      "end_time": 169448.0,
      "text": "we decided with Jean-François Brunet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 169472.0,
      "end_time": 171385.0,
      "text": "who is a colleague of mine, a biologist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 171409.0,
      "end_time": 172583.0,
      "text": "to study them."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 173379.0,
      "end_time": 175149.0,
      "text": "What do I mean by that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 175174.0,
      "end_time": 179207.0,
      "text": "We wanted to grow cells from these pieces of tissue."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 180484.0,
      "end_time": 181903.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not an easy task."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 182577.0,
      "end_time": 184942.0,
      "text": "Growing cells from a piece of tissue"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 184966.0,
      "end_time": 188425.0,
      "text": "is a bit the same as growing very small children"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 188449.0,
      "end_time": 189919.0,
      "text": "out from their family."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 191689.0,
      "end_time": 194600.0,
      "text": "So you need to find the right nutrients,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 194300.0,
      "end_time": 195799.0,
      "text": "the warmth, the humidity"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 195823.0,
      "end_time": 199590.0,
      "text": "and all the nice environments to make them thrive."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 199830.0,
      "end_time": 201894.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s exactly what we had to do with these cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 202425.0,
      "end_time": 204291.0,
      "text": "And after many attempts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 204959.0,
      "end_time": 206726.0,
      "text": "Jean-François did it."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 207372.0,
      "end_time": 210569.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s what he saw under his microscope."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 211691.0,
      "end_time": 214390.0,
      "text": "And that was, for us, a major surprise."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 214412.0,
      "end_time": 215563.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 215587.0,
      "end_time": 220429.0,
      "text": "Because this looks exactly the same as a stem cell culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 220453.0,
      "end_time": 226960.0,
      "text": "with large green cells surrounding small, immature cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 227168.0,
      "end_time": 230422.0,
      "text": "And you may remember from biology class"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 230446.0,
      "end_time": 233957.0,
      "text": "that stem cells are immature cells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 233981.0,
      "end_time": 237859.0,
      "text": "able to turn into any type of cell of the body."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 239423.0,
      "end_time": 244510.0,
      "text": "The adult brain has stem cells, but they&#39;re very rare"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 244750.0,
      "end_time": 248453.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re located in deep and small niches"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 248478.0,
      "end_time": 250495.0,
      "text": "in the depths of the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 250519.0,
      "end_time": 254221.0,
      "text": "So it was surprising to get this kind of stem cell culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 254245.0,
      "end_time": 256603.0,
      "text": "from the superficial part of swollen brain we had"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 256628.0,
      "end_time": 258245.0,
      "text": "in the operating theater."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 258269.0,
      "end_time": 260875.0,
      "text": "And there was another intriguing observation:"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 261890.0,
      "end_time": 266116.0,
      "text": "Regular stem cells are very active cells --"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 266140.0,
      "end_time": 269712.0,
      "text": "cells that divide, divide, divide very quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 270409.0,
      "end_time": 272729.0,
      "text": "And they never die, they&#39;re immortal cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 273407.0,
      "end_time": 275798.0,
      "text": "But these cells behave differently."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 276663.0,
      "end_time": 278846.0,
      "text": "They divide slowly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 278870.0,
      "end_time": 280870.0,
      "text": "and after a few weeks of culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 280894.0,
      "end_time": 282456.0,
      "text": "they even died."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 283321.0,
      "end_time": 286973.0,
      "text": "So we were in front of a strange new cell population"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 286997.0,
      "end_time": 290910.0,
      "text": "that looked like stem cells but behaved differently."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 291520.0,
      "end_time": 295496.0,
      "text": "And it took us a long time to understand where they came from."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 295520.0,
      "end_time": 298650.0,
      "text": "They come from these cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 298550.0,
      "end_time": 302993.0,
      "text": "These blue and red cells are called doublecortin-positive cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 304195.0,
      "end_time": 306747.0,
      "text": "All of you have them in your brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 307353.0,
      "end_time": 311253.0,
      "text": "They represent four percent of your cortical brain cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 311857.0,
      "end_time": 315929.0,
      "text": "They have a very important role during the development stage."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 315953.0,
      "end_time": 317707.0,
      "text": "When you were fetuses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 318457.0,
      "end_time": 321129.0,
      "text": "they helped your brain to fold itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 322120.0,
      "end_time": 324635.0,
      "text": "But why do they stay in your head?"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 325371.0,
      "end_time": 326777.0,
      "text": "This, we don&#39;t know."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 327414.0,
      "end_time": 330635.0,
      "text": "We think that they may participate in brain repair"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 330660.0,
      "end_time": 334124.0,
      "text": "because we find them in higher concentration"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 334148.0,
      "end_time": 335300.0,
      "text": "close to brain lesions."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 335324.0,
      "end_time": 336942.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s not so sure."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 337867.0,
      "end_time": 340212.0,
      "text": "But there is one clear thing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 340236.0,
      "end_time": 341832.0,
      "text": "that from these cells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 341857.0,
      "end_time": 344950.0,
      "text": "we got our stem cell culture."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 345363.0,
      "end_time": 347997.0,
      "text": "And we were in front of a potential new source of cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 348210.0,
      "end_time": 349472.0,
      "text": "to repair the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 350400.0,
      "end_time": 351561.0,
      "text": "And we had to prove this."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 351585.0,
      "end_time": 352736.0,
      "text": "So to prove it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 352760.0,
      "end_time": 356608.0,
      "text": "we decided to design an experimental paradigm."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 356632.0,
      "end_time": 359855.0,
      "text": "The idea was to biopsy a piece of brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 359879.0,
      "end_time": 362578.0,
      "text": "in a non-eloquent area of the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 362602.0,
      "end_time": 364313.0,
      "text": "and then to culture the cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 364337.0,
      "end_time": 367123.0,
      "text": "exactly the way Jean-François did it in his lab."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 367148.0,
      "end_time": 370430.0,
      "text": "And then label them, to put color in them"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 370670.0,
      "end_time": 372740.0,
      "text": "in order to be able to track them in the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 373295.0,
      "end_time": 375424.0,
      "text": "And the last step was to re-implant them"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 375448.0,
      "end_time": 377231.0,
      "text": "in the same individual."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 377255.0,
      "end_time": 378406.0,
      "text": "We call these"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 378430.0,
      "end_time": 381231.0,
      "text": "autologous grafts -- autografts."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 381602.0,
      "end_time": 384440.0,
      "text": "So the first question we had,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 384690.0,
      "end_time": 389310.0,
      "text": "\"What will happen if we re-implant these cells in a normal brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 389334.0,
      "end_time": 392192.0,
      "text": "and what will happen if we re-implant the same cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 392216.0,
      "end_time": 393439.0,
      "text": "in a lesioned brain?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 393463.0,
      "end_time": 396852.0,
      "text": "Thanks to the help of professor Eric Rouiller,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 396876.0,
      "end_time": 398542.0,
      "text": "we worked with monkeys."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 399414.0,
      "end_time": 401854.0,
      "text": "So in the first-case scenario,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 401878.0,
      "end_time": 405383.0,
      "text": "we re-implanted the cells in the normal brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 405407.0,
      "end_time": 410442.0,
      "text": "and what we saw is that they completely disappeared after a few weeks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 410466.0,
      "end_time": 413420.0,
      "text": "as if they were taken from the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 413444.0,
      "end_time": 414955.0,
      "text": "they go back home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 414979.0,
      "end_time": 416534.0,
      "text": "the space is already busy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 416559.0,
      "end_time": 418789.0,
      "text": "they are not needed there, so they disappear."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 419780.0,
      "end_time": 421758.0,
      "text": "In the second-case scenario,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 421782.0,
      "end_time": 423130.0,
      "text": "we performed the lesion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 423370.0,
      "end_time": 426176.0,
      "text": "we re-implanted exactly the same cells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 426201.0,
      "end_time": 430274.0,
      "text": "and in this case, the cells remained --"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 430298.0,
      "end_time": 433950.0,
      "text": "and they became mature neurons."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 433824.0,
      "end_time": 437611.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s the image of what we could observe under the microscope."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 437635.0,
      "end_time": 440188.0,
      "text": "Those are the cells that were re-implanted."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 440839.0,
      "end_time": 442786.0,
      "text": "And the proof they carry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 442810.0,
      "end_time": 445987.0,
      "text": "these little spots, those are the cells that we&#39;ve labeled"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 446110.0,
      "end_time": 448843.0,
      "text": "in vitro, when they were in culture."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 449755.0,
      "end_time": 451955.0,
      "text": "But we could not stop here, of course."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 452521.0,
      "end_time": 457158.0,
      "text": "Do these cells also help a monkey to recover after a lesion?"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 457182.0,
      "end_time": 462664.0,
      "text": "So for that, we trained monkeys to perform a manual dexterity task."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 462688.0,
      "end_time": 465705.0,
      "text": "They had to retrieve food pellets from a tray."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 465730.0,
      "end_time": 467225.0,
      "text": "They were very good at it."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 467896.0,
      "end_time": 471368.0,
      "text": "And when they had reached a plateau of performance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 471392.0,
      "end_time": 477687.0,
      "text": "we did a lesion in the motor cortex corresponding to the hand motion."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 477711.0,
      "end_time": 479568.0,
      "text": "So the monkeys were plegic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 479592.0,
      "end_time": 481503.0,
      "text": "they could not move their hand anymore."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 482165.0,
      "end_time": 485719.0,
      "text": "And exactly the same as humans would do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 485743.0,
      "end_time": 488669.0,
      "text": "they spontaneously recovered to a certain extent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 488693.0,
      "end_time": 490712.0,
      "text": "exactly the same as after a stroke."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 490737.0,
      "end_time": 492524.0,
      "text": "Patients are completely plegic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 492548.0,
      "end_time": 497656.0,
      "text": "and then they try to recover due to a brain plasticity mechanism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 497680.0,
      "end_time": 499320.0,
      "text": "they recover to a certain extent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 499344.0,
      "end_time": 501185.0,
      "text": "exactly the same for the monkey."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 501209.0,
      "end_time": 504653.0,
      "text": "So when we were sure that the monkey had reached his plateau"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 504677.0,
      "end_time": 507105.0,
      "text": "of spontaneous recovery,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 507129.0,
      "end_time": 509704.0,
      "text": "we implanted his own cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 510287.0,
      "end_time": 515823.0,
      "text": "So on the left side, you see the monkey that has spontaneously recovered."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 517426.00000000006,
      "end_time": 522580.00000000006,
      "text": "He&#39;s at about 40 to 50 percent of his previous performance"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 522820.00000000006,
      "end_time": 523294.00000000006,
      "text": "before the lesion."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 524780.0,
      "end_time": 526848.0,
      "text": "He&#39;s not so accurate, not so quick."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 527376.0,
      "end_time": 530834.0,
      "text": "And look now when we re-implant the cells:"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 530859.0,
      "end_time": 535112.0,
      "text": "Two months after re-implantation, the same individual."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 537255.0,
      "end_time": 544173.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 544770.0,
      "end_time": 548324.0,
      "text": "It was also very exciting results for us, I tell you."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 549321.0,
      "end_time": 553270.0,
      "text": "Since that time, we&#39;ve understood much more about these cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 553575.0,
      "end_time": 555971.0,
      "text": "We know that we can cryopreserve them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 555995.0,
      "end_time": 557857.0,
      "text": "we can use them later on."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 558214.0,
      "end_time": 562104.0,
      "text": "We know that we can apply them in other neuropathological models,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 562128.0,
      "end_time": 564970.0,
      "text": "like Parkinson&#39;s disease, for example."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 564121.0,
      "end_time": 567278.0,
      "text": "But our dream is still to implant them in humans."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 568469.0,
      "end_time": 572219.0,
      "text": "And I really hope that I&#39;ll be able to show you soon"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 573605.0,
      "end_time": 578599.0,
      "text": "that the human brain is giving us the tools to repair itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 578623.0,
      "end_time": 579943.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 579967.0,
      "end_time": 585953.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 585977.0,
      "end_time": 589279.0,
      "text": "Bruno Giussani: Jocelyne, this is amazing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 589303.0,
      "end_time": 593540.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m sure that right now, there are several dozen people in the audience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 593780.0,
      "end_time": 594284.0,
      "text": "possibly even a majority,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 594308.0,
      "end_time": 597560.0,
      "text": "who are thinking, \"I know somebody who can use this.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 597800.0,
      "end_time": 599340.0,
      "text": "I do, in any case."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 599364.0,
      "end_time": 601660.0,
      "text": "And of course the question is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 601684.0,
      "end_time": 603762.0,
      "text": "what are the biggest obstacles"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 603786.0,
      "end_time": 606577.0,
      "text": "before you can go into human clinical trials?"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 607665.0,
      "end_time": 613170.0,
      "text": "Jocelyne Bloch: The biggest obstacles are regulations. (Laughs)"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 613195.0,
      "end_time": 615957.0,
      "text": "So, from these exciting results, you need to fill out"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 615981.0,
      "end_time": 619218.0,
      "text": "about two kilograms of papers and forms"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 619242.0,
      "end_time": 622290.0,
      "text": "to be able to go through these kind of trials."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 622314.0,
      "end_time": 624945.0,
      "text": "BG: Which is understandable, the brain is delicate, etc."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 624970.0,
      "end_time": 627328.0,
      "text": "JB: Yes, it is, but it takes a long time"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 627352.0,
      "end_time": 631382.0,
      "text": "and a lot of patience and almost a professional team to do it, you know?"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 631407.0,
      "end_time": 633673.0,
      "text": "BG: If you project yourself --"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 633697.0,
      "end_time": 634912.0,
      "text": "having done the research"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 634936.0,
      "end_time": 638881.0,
      "text": "and having tried to get permission to start the trials,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 638905.0,
      "end_time": 642840.0,
      "text": "if you project yourself out in time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 642736.0,
      "end_time": 646434.0,
      "text": "how many years before somebody gets into a hospital"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 646458.0,
      "end_time": 648631.0,
      "text": "and this therapy is available?"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 649555.0,
      "end_time": 651689.0,
      "text": "JB: So, it&#39;s very difficult to say."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 651714.0,
      "end_time": 655648.0,
      "text": "It depends, first, on the approval of the trial."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 655672.0,
      "end_time": 658775.0,
      "text": "Will the regulation allow us to do it soon?"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 658799.0,
      "end_time": 661613.0,
      "text": "And then, you have to perform this kind of study"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 661637.0,
      "end_time": 664436.0,
      "text": "in a small group of patients."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 664461.0,
      "end_time": 667386.0,
      "text": "So it takes, already, a long time to select the patients,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 667410.0,
      "end_time": 669315.0,
      "text": "do the treatment"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 669340.0,
      "end_time": 673690.0,
      "text": "and evaluate if it&#39;s useful to do this kind of treatment."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 673930.0,
      "end_time": 677752.0,
      "text": "And then you have to deploy this to a multicentric trial."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 677776.0,
      "end_time": 681938.0,
      "text": "You have to really prove first that it&#39;s useful"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 681962.0,
      "end_time": 684843.0,
      "text": "before offering this treatment up for everybody."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 684867.0,
      "end_time": 686756.0,
      "text": "BG: And safe, of course. JB: Of course."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 686780.0,
      "end_time": 689574.0,
      "text": "BG: Jocelyne, thank you for coming to TED and sharing this."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 689598.0,
      "end_time": 690748.0,
      "text": "BG: Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 690773.0,
      "end_time": 693444.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}